50|$|Conscientious {{objection}} to military taxation (COMT) {{is a legal}} theory that attempts to extend {{into the realm of}} taxation the concessions to <b>conscientious</b> <b>objectors</b> that many governments allow in the case of conscription, thereby allowing <b>conscientious</b> <b>objectors</b> to insist that their tax payments not be spent for military purposes.|$|R
