5|$|Some 843 <b>conscientious</b> <b>objectors</b> {{spent more}} than two years in prison; ten died while there, {{seventeen}} were initially given the death penalty (but received life imprisonment) and 142 were imprisoned on life sentences. <b>Conscientious</b> <b>objectors</b> who were deemed not to have made any useful contribution were disenfranchised for five years after the war.|$|R
